    "answer_id" : 58693616,
    "question_id" : 9966053,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Not least important is why these symbols occur in url.\nSee <a href=\"https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.parse-str.php#76792\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.parse-str.php#76792</a>, specifically:</p>\n\n<pre><code>parse_str('foo[]=1&amp;foo[]=2&amp;foo[]=3', $bar);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>the above produces:</p>\n\n<pre><code>$bar = ['foo' =&gt; ['1', '2', '3'] ];\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and what is THE method to separate query vars in arrays (in php, at least).</p>\n"
  }, {
